-- Akfen Gains in Istanbul After Report on TAV Insaat Contract
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2012-04-25T10:16:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-25/akfen-gains-in-istanbul-after-report-on-tav-insaat-contract.html
Akfen Holding AS (AKFEN) , a Turkish
builder, climbed in Istanbul after Reuters reported Akfen’s unit
TAV Insaat and partners may win a contract valued at about $3
billion in  Abu Dhabi .  Akfen rose 3.4 percent to 9.62 liras at the 12:30 p.m.
midday close, in the biggest increase since April 13. A group
including Arabtec Holding PJSC, TAV Insaat and Consolidated
Contractors Co. may win the contract for the expansion of Abu
Dhabi’s international airport, Reuters reported, citing people
it didn’t identify.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
